<subsection xml:id="subsec-hire-purchase-2">
  <title>Hire purchase</title>
   <p>Visit a nearby Electronic or general shop with your teacher or quardian or parent and ask for prices of different Items when bought with cash money and also when purchased by paying a small deposit and paying the rest of the remaining funds monthly according to agreed terms and conditions. What do you notice?</p>
  <activity>
    <statement>
     <p>
         Consider a motorist buying a Motorcycle at Ksh. 150,000 on hire purhase terms. He pays a deposit of  Sh.40,000 and the remaining money will be paid by monthly instalments of 10,500 for 10 months. What was the total cost of the Motorcycle?
     </p>
     <p> Identify the cashprice of the Motorcycle. </p>
     <p>
      Calculate the total amount the motorist paid for the vehicle.
     </p>
     <p>
      How much money could have been saved if the Motorist bought the motorcycle with cash?
     </p>
     <p>
      Discuss with your friends 3 advantages and 3 disadvantages of buying items in hire purchase terms.
     </p>
    </statement>
  </activity>
  <example>
    <statement>
      <p>
        The cash price of a rectangular water storage tank was Ksh. 120,000. Kerubo paid a deposit of Ksh. 30,000 and 12 monthly instalments of Ksh.9,000 per month.
      </p>
      <p>
       (a) Calculate the hire purchase price.

      </p>
      <p>
        (b) Calculate the deposit if he could have paid monthly instalments of Ksh. 15,000 for 6 months.
      </p>
      <p>
        (c) How much more money did Kerubo pay in Hire purchase than cash price?
      </p>
    </statement>
  </example>

</subsection>